{"lemma":"رَبَّةُ","slug":"رَبَّةُ","root":"ر.ب.ب","root_slug":"ر-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَبّ","root":"ربب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":975},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["adj","adv","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":19},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14358","n14371","n14372","n14373","n14624"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be master, to be lord"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have possession, to gather, to control"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have authority over, to govern"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to impact, to comprise, to contain"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to collect, to congregate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grow, to increase, to become greater"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bring up, to raise (a child)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"master, lord, king, sovereign, potentate","examples":[{"text":"رَبُّ الدَّار","english":"master of the house"},{"text":"رَبُّ الْعَائِلَة","english":"paterfamilias"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Lord, an epithet of God","examples":[{"text":"اَللهُ رَبُّ الْعَالَمِين","english":"God is Lord of the Worlds"},{"text":"الرَّبّ","english":"the LORD"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"god, deity","examples":[{"text":"يَا صَاحِبَيِ السِّجْنِ أَأَرْبَابٌ مُّتَفَرِّقُونَ خَيْرٌ أَمِ اللّٰهُ الْوَاحِدُ الْقَهَّارُ","english":"[Joseph said:] \"O my two companions of the prison! Are many different deities better than God the One [Who is the Source of all things], the Overpowering?\""}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"leader, chief, head","examples":[{"text":"رَبُّ بَحْرِيّ","english":"seaman (naval rank)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"owner, proprietor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"one possessed of, one endowed with"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"having to do with"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَبَّ (rabba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thickened fruit juice, thickened juice"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mash, pulp"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"many","examples":[{"text":"رُبَّ رَجُلٍ","english":"many a man"},{"text":"رُبَّ مَرَّةٍ","english":"many a time"}]},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"likely, perhaps, mayhap, potentially"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *rabb-."},"ipa":["/rab.ba/","/rabb/","/rubb/","/rub.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14358","headword_ar":"رَبَّهُ","root":"rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~N","text_ar":"رَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~","text_ar":"رَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lord, possessor, owner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he possessed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"owned, it; had possession of it, and command,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"authority, over it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) namely, a thing; (K;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malakahu","text_ar":"مَلَكَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) [And in like manner,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~","text_ar":"رَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rababotu Alqawoma","text_ar":"رَبَبْتُ القَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [inf. n. as above and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marab~apN","text_ar":"مَرَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbapN","text_ar":"رِبَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I ruled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"governed, the people;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"susotuhumo","text_ar":"سُسْتُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, over them"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as their lord, master,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAlato marab~atuhumu Aln~aAsa","text_ar":"طَالَتْ مَرَبَّتُهُمُ النَّاسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbatuhum","text_ar":"رِبَابَتُهُم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Their ruling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"governing, the people continued long."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K. *) The saying of Safwán, (T, S,) on the day of Honeyn, (T,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^ano yarub~aniY rajulN mino qurayo$K A^aHab~u A_ilaY~a","text_ar":"لَاَنْ يَرُبَّنِى رَجُلٌ مِنْ قُرَيْشٍ اَحَبُّ اـِلَىَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^uno yarub~aniY rajulN mino hawaAzina","text_ar":"مِنْ اُنْ يَرُبَّنِى رَجُلٌ مِنْ هَوَازِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Assuredly that a man of Kureysh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"should be over me"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S) as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~","text_ar":"رَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as master,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief, having command,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"authority, over me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is more pleasing to me than that a man of Hawázin should be lord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over me."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-  Also, (S, M, Mgh, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~N","text_ar":"رَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He reared, fostered, brought up, fed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nourished, him; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~aAhu","text_ar":"رَبَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Mgh, K;) namely, his child, (S,) or a child, (M, K,) either his own or another's;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking good care of him, and acting as his guardian,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until he attained to puberty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the utmost term of youth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rb~bhu","text_ar":"ربّبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, S, M, Mgh, K,) or this has a more emphatic signification, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarbiybN","text_ar":"تَربِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M, Mgh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarib~apN","text_ar":"تَرِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, M, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trb~bh","text_ar":"تربّبه","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Artb~hu","text_ar":"ارتبّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) [in like manner, also,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raboraba","text_ar":"رَبْرَبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he reared, fostered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brought up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"an orphan: (AA, T:) and accord. to IDrd, (M,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabibotuhu","text_ar":"رَبِبْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. var. [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rababo=tuhu","text_ar":"رَبَبْ=تُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, K:) he says also that the verb is used in like manner in relation to the young one of an animal other than man; and he used to cite this ex.:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kaAna lanaA wahowa faluw~N nirobibuho"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He belonged to us when he was a young weaned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one-year-old, colt, we rearing him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; with the letter characteristic of the aor. meksoor, to show that the second letter of the preterite is meksoor, accord to the opinion of Sb in respect of a case of this kind; and this, he says, is peculiar to the dial. of Hudheyl in this species of verb. (M, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~ati AlmaroA^apu Sabiy~ahaA","text_ar":"رَبَّتِ المَرْاَةُ صَبِيَّهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", used tropically, means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The woman patted her child repeatedly on its side in order that it might sleep."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) [See 2 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbt","text_ar":"ربت"},{"kind":"text","text":".] [It is said that] the primary signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ab~u","text_ar":"الرَّبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~arobiyapu","text_ar":"التَّرْبِيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e. The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bringing"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a state of completion by degrees."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in i. l.) A poet says, (S,) namely, Hassán Ibn-Thábit, (TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"mino dur~apK bayoDaA='a SaAfiyapK\n                      \n                     \n                        HaAy^iru AlbaHori ↓ \n      mim~aA tarab~aba"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Than a white, clear, pearl, of those which the depth of the sea has brought to maturity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning a pearl which the shell has reared, or brought to maturity in the bottom of the water. (S, TA.) And the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka niEomapN tarub~uhaA","text_ar":"لَكَ نِعْمَةٌ تَرُبُّهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in a trad., meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast wealth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which thou preservest, and of which thou takest care, and which thou fosterest like as the man fosters his child."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaTaru yarub~u Aln~abaAta waAlv~araY","text_ar":"المَطَرُ يَرُبُّ النَّبَاتَ وَالثَّرَى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rain causes the plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, and the moisture"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to increase."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aHaAbu yarub~u AlmaTara","text_ar":"السَّحَابُ يَرُبُّ المَطَرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The clouds collect and increase the rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~a","text_ar":"رَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~N","text_ar":"رَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbN","text_ar":"رِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbapN","text_ar":"رِبَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, M, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rb~b","text_ar":"ربّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, TA;) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He increased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rightly disposed, and completed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S,) a benefit, or benefaction. (T, S, M, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~a AlA^amora","text_ar":"رَبَّ الاَمْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~N","text_ar":"رَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbapN","text_ar":"رِبَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put the affair into a right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or proper, state; adjusted it, arranged it, ordered it, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rightly disposed it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and established it firmly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he managed, conducted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regulated, the affair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) [perhaps from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~a","text_ar":"رَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ he reared, ” &c.; but more probably, I think, from what next follows.] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~a","text_ar":"رَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~u","text_ar":"رَبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~N","text_ar":"رُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rb~b","text_ar":"ربّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He seasoned"},{"kind":"text","text":"a skin (T, S, K) for clarified butter (T, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~","text_ar":"رُبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rob,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inspissated juice"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (T, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of dates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) which imparts a good odour to it, (S, TA,) and prevents the flavour and odour of the butter from being spoiled: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he seasoned"},{"kind":"text","text":"a skin with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~","text_ar":"رُبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and a jar with tar or pitch: or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rababotuhu","text_ar":"رَبَبْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I smeared it over, and prepared it properly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~a","text_ar":"رَبَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rb~b","text_ar":"ربّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or the latter, but the former also is allowable, (M,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made"},{"kind":"text","text":"oil, or ointment,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good, and sweet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fragrant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he perfumed"},{"kind":"text","text":"it, (M, K, * TA,) accord. to Lh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by infusing in it jasmine or some other sweet-smelling"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1003},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murab~abN","text_ar":"مُرَبَّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below. ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~a","text_ar":"رَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He collected, or congregated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) people: (TA:) [and so, probably, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rb~b","text_ar":"ربّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rababN","text_ar":"رَبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yarub~u Aln~aAsa","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَرُبُّ النَّاسَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one collects,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"congregates, to him the people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~a","text_ar":"رَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~ato","text_ar":"رَبَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the M,) or"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~N","text_ar":"رَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbN","text_ar":"رِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, [in each of which this is mentioned as the inf. n. whence the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~aY","text_ar":"رُبَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) said of a ewe or she-goat,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She brought forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she conceived:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to some, there is no verb to the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~aY","text_ar":"رُبَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) AZ says that it has no verb: (Msb:) [but] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbN","text_ar":"رِبَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n. used in relation to a ewe or she-goat as meaning her"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being in the state of such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~aY","text_ar":"رُبَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (S, M, * Msb, * K: *) and in relation to a she-camel, as in the ex. cited by Munteji' Ibn-Nebhán to As,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Haniyna A^um~i Albaw~ifiY ribaAbihaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The yearning cry of the mother of the young camel in the time of her having recently brought forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) and used also in relation to a woman as meaning her"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having recently brought forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her state within two months after having brought forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"within twenty days:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence the phrase, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoluhaA ribaAbN","text_ar":"حَمْلُهَا رِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She becomes pregnant soon after having brought forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","T","S","Mgh","Lh","TA","AA","Msb","MF"]},{"entry_id":"n14371","headword_ar":"رَبَّةٌ","root":"rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~N","text_ar":"رَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ab~apu","text_ar":"الرَّبَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"was also the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A Kaabeh"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"square temple"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in Nejrán,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belonging to"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tribe of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Medh-hij"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and Benu-l-Hárith-Ibn-Kaab, who held it in honour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) In a trad. of 'Orweh (K, TA) Ibn-Mes'ood Eth-Thakafee, (TA,) it is applied"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to El-Lát"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~aAtu","text_ar":"اللَّاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rock which"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tribe of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thakeef worshipped, at Et-Táïf."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And in another trad., it is said to be the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A temple of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tribe of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thakeef, which, when they became Muslims, was demolished by El-Mugheereh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~apN","text_ar":"رَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArN rab~apN","text_ar":"دَارٌ رَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A large house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mansion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~aY","text_ar":"رُبَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["M","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n14372","headword_ar":"رُبَّةٌ","root":"rb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A party, division, sect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinct body"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"class, of men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large assembly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a myriad;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ten thousand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereabout:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rib~pN","text_ar":"رِبّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (M, K:) or this signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of men"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T:) the pl. of the former is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbN","text_ar":"رِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M:) and that of the latter is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arib~apN","text_ar":"اَرِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, K:) by Th [and in the K], the former pl. is said to be a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rib~apN","text_ar":"رِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is a mistake. (M.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbN","text_ar":"رِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Companions."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And hence [also], i. e., as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ubapu","text_ar":"الرُّبَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ibaAbu","text_ar":"الرِّبَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confederate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tribes of Dabbeh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Teym and 'Adee and 'Okl;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Teym and 'Adee and 'Owf and Thowr and Ashyab;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA; [but for the orthography of the last of these names I have found no authority; it is written in the TA"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$yb","text_ar":"اشيب"},{"kind":"text","text":", without any syll. signs;]) and Dabbeh was their paternal uncle; (TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"five tribes which united in a confederacy, consisting of Dabbeh and Thowr and 'Okl and Teym and 'Adee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) they were thus called because of their division into distinct bodies; (M;) or because they collected themselves (As, Th, S, TA) in distinct bodies: (Th, M, TA:) or because they united in a confederacy against Temeem Ibn-Murr: (AO, M, TA:) or because they dipped their hands in some"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~","text_ar":"رُبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and formed a confederacy over it: (As, T, M, K:) or, as some say, because they congregated, and became like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAb","text_ar":"رِبَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or bundle] of arrows [used in the game called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almayosir","text_ar":"المَيْسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) the rel. n. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~iY~N","text_ar":"رُبِّىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", formed from the sing., (Sb, S, M,) accord. to a rule generally observed except when a [single] man has a pl. word for his name, as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kilaAbN","text_ar":"كِلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (S, TA.) ―         -b4-  The sing. ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~apN","text_ar":"رُبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Plenty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundance, of the means of subsistence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inseparable, prosperity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Khálid Ibn-Jembeh, TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~aY","text_ar":"رُبَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["M","K","T","S","As","Th","TA","AO","Sb"]},{"entry_id":"n14373","headword_ar":"رِبَّةٌ","root":"rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, first sentence. ―         -b2-  [Hence its pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arib~apN","text_ar":"اَرِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Confederates;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, IB, K;) [or] it is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awuw A^arib~apK","text_ar":"ذَوُو اَرِبَّةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having covenants;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arib~apN","text_ar":"اَرِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being said by AAF to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbN","text_ar":"رِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EahodN","text_ar":"عَهْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IB, TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"season called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remaining in the end of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a number of plants which do not dry up in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remaining green in the winter and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Syf","text_ar":"صيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"summer"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among which are the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hul~ab","text_ar":"حُلَّب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruxaAmaY","text_ar":"رُخَامَى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makor","text_ar":"مَكْر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaloqaY","text_ar":"عَلْقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaloqFY","text_ar":"عَلْقًى"},{"kind":"text","text":": [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabolN","text_ar":"رَبْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender, herb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any plant that is green in the hot season:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain species of trees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of plants, undefined:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribabN","text_ar":"رِبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb.) [In the dial. of Egypt,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Alexandrian trefoil"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birosiym","text_ar":"بِرْسِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the second and third crops."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as some say, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tree of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xar~uwb","text_ar":"خَرُّوب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an appellation generally applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carob,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"locust-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n14624","headword_ar":"رُبَةٌ","root":"rbw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabowN","text_ar":"رَبْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}